Heat the oven to 220C/425F/Gas 7.Blend the bread, cream, plaice, dill and egg in a food processor.Pour into a lined and greased round ramekin dish and place in a bain-marie.Bake in the oven for 8-10 minutes.For the cream, place the cream and juice in a saucepan. Bring to the boil and reduce for 1-2 minutes.Turn out onto a plate and drizzle with orange cream.